<http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlab093>
    bibo:endPage "1146" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-12-16" ;
    bibo:startPage "1116" ;
    bibo:volume "195" ;
    dc:creator "Almón, Bruno; Cuesta, Jose A.; Schubart, Christoph D.; Armenia, Lisa; García-Raso, J. Enrique" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of the hermit crab Diogenes pugilator (Decapoda: Anomura) reveals the existence of a species complex in the Atlanto-Mediterranean transition zone, resulting in the resurrection of D. curvimanus and the description of a new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993815>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993817>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993828> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993815>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Diogenes pugilator s.s. ♂ 3.0 mm, Frontignan, France, neotype, (MNHN-IU-2019-3215): A, anterior part of body; B, ophtalmic scales; E, right cheliped, outer aspect; F, telson, dorsal aspect. Diogenes pugilator s.s. ♂ 2.7 mm, Frontignan, France, topotype (ZSMA2019 0400): C, right antennular, inner view; D, left maxiliped 3, (inset: detail of the spines, ventral aspect). (Scales: A, C, E = 1 mm, B, D, F = 0.5 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6993815/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993817>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Diogenes pugilator s.s. ♂ 3.0 mm, Frontignan, France, neotype, (MNHN-IU-2019-3215): A, left cheliped, outer aspect (arrow indicating bispinose protuberance); B, left cheliped, dorsal aspect (inset: detail of the row of tubercles on the lower, inner surface). Diogenes pugilator s.s. ♀ 2.5 mm, La Carihuela, Málaga, Spain, topotype, (IEOCD-BR/2660-2661): C, left cheliped, outer aspect. Diogenes pugilator s.s. ♂ 2.7 mm Frontignan, France, topotype, (ZSMA2019 0400): D, left pereiopod 2 (insets: variations in P3 carpus; dactylus inner aspect); E, pereiopod 4; F, merus, mesial view (setae omitted). (Scales: A–C, F = 2 mm, D = 1 mm, E = 0.5 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6993817/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6993828>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Live coloration of the three species of Diogenes: A–C, left cheliped, outer aspect; D–F, cephalothorax and cephalic appendages; G–I, detailed photographs of the inner face of palms, showing the shape of the row of tubercles; J–L, left pereiopod 2. A, D, G, J, Diogenes pugilator; B, E, H, K, Diogenes armatus sp. nov. C, F, I, L, Diogenes curvimanus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6993828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

